msgid "Sync normalizes catalogs with stable output rules (`msgcat --sort-output --no-wrap --add-location=file`), so diffs stay focused on real source changes. Unavoidable churn: header metadata (`POT-Creation-Date` etc.), reference-location updates when a string moves files, and actual source-string edits."
